channel.title: Interleaved RSS Feed
channel.description: This is an interleaved feed of the most recent entries from each RSS source, skipping any feeds with errors.

item.title: Jurors on Hunter Biden Gun Case Were Split at First, but Overwhelming Drug Evidence Swayed the Panel
Jury likely considered Hunter Biden’s own words in memoir as ‘powerful’ evidence to convict: experts
item.description: Following the Hunter Biden's guilty verdict, some legal experts pointed to his own memoir of his drug addiction recovery as “powerful" evidence for the jury to convict him.

item.title: Biden Admin to Close ICE Facility in Dilley, Texas
item.description: Biden administration will close a facility used by Immigration and Customs Enforcement in Dilley, Texas, to detain families and single adults found illegally crossing the U.S. southern border, The Wall Street Journal reported.

item.title: Ex-NY Governor Cuomo to Answer to House Subcommittee on COVID Nursing Home Debacle
Republicans vow to continue pursuing 'Biden crime family' after Hunter Biden's guilty verdict
item.description: Republican reactions to Tuesday's verdict in Hunter Biden's federal gun trial rolled in as lawmakers urged continued scrutiny of "the Biden crime family."

item.title: Report: Patagonia Sent Thousands to Palestinian Terror Groups
item.description: Patagonia, the U.S.-based outdoor clothing retailer, funneled tens of thousands of dollars to a progressive organization linked to Palestinian terror groups, according to the Washington Examiner.

item.title: No, the Hunter Biden Verdict Wasn't About 'Fairness'—and What About That Pardon?
UN Security Council passes US-backed Gaza cease-fire proposal
item.description: The United Nations Security Council voted 14-0 in favor of a U.S. cease-fire proposal for Gaza on Monday, with both Israel and Hamas favoring the deal.

item.title: Attorney: IRS Whistleblowers Helped Expose Hunter Biden
item.description: If not for two IRS whistleblowers, Hunter Biden might never have been brought to justice.

item.title: SC David Weiss: Case Was Not Just About Addiction but About Illegal Choices Made by Hunter Biden
Hunter Biden trial juror says he didn't buy defense's 7-Eleven story
item.description: A juror in Hunter Biden's gun crime trial said the case was "heart-wrenching," but ultimately "nobody is above the law," in comments after Biden was found guilty on all counts.

item.title: Biden Admin to Chop Medical Debt From Credit Reports
item.description: The Biden administration will announce a new rule Tuesday to ban medical debt from credit reports in effort to convince voters the White House is looking to improve financial opportunities for Americans.

item.title: FARCE: DNC to Reimburse White House for Tiny, Tiny Percentage of Jill Biden's Paris-Delaware Trial Trips
Trump within striking distance of Biden in competitive blue-leaning state: poll
item.description: A new poll in longtime blue-leaning Minnesota shows a competitive race between President Biden and former President Trump in their 2024 election rematch.

item.title: Trump Campaign: Hunter Trial 'Distraction' From Father
item.description: Former President Donald Trump's campaign Tuesday, after a Delaware jury convicted Hunter Biden of all three felony charges in his federal gun trial, slammed the proceedings as being a "distraction" from the activities of President Joe Biden and his family members.
